Description: Code Analysis Server - MCP server for code analysis and refactoring
 A comprehensive Python code analysis and refactoring tool that generates code
 maps, detects issues, and provides automated refactoring capabilities.
 .
 Features:
  - Code mapping and dependency analysis
  - Issue detection and code quality checks
  - Semantic search using FAISS vector index
  - Automated refactoring (class splitting, superclass extraction)
  - SQLite database for fast indexed storage
  - MCP (Model Context Protocol) server interface
  - File watching and automatic indexing
  - Vectorization and embedding support
 .
 This package installs code-analysis-server as a systemd service with
 configuration in /etc/code-analysis-server/ and data in /var/lib/code-analysis-server/.

